Years later, she is found by her son, now a teenager, who tells her that Wolf Daddy has asked for her to come back to the Demon World. Origin

Randolph Thompson is the first in line to be Mayor of Buzztown. He killed his wife Teresa Thompson with a couple of bookends, for nagging him. He later dumped her body in a river. In an attempt to kill the real Mayor the body of his wife was found by a police officer who was helping him. Upon seeing the corpse of Teresa, the officer has a change of heart and is shot in the head by Randolph.

It is at this time that the Madman stops Randolph and rescues the Mayor. A fight between the Madman and Randolph ends with the assistant of Teresa and the officer's corpses whom come from the dead and drag Randolph down into the river with them.

deck: If a prisoner in the jail known as "Liz's Toy Box" wish to leave, all he have to do is fight and defeat the imortal Zombie Brothers.
description:
In the infamous Demon World prison known as "Liz's Toy Box," all the prisoners can leave if they press the "challenge button" in their cell. By doing so, they challenge the Zombie Brothers to battle. If the prisoner can defeat the brothers in combat, he will be free to go. But that is easier said than done, since the brothers are unkillarble.

The only person who ever gained his freedom by defeating them, is Staz Blood.

Powers & Abilities

The Zombie Brothers super-strong, surprisingly fast, and can survive any kind of attack, since they are already dead. They also have perfect control over their entire body, and can therefor move their body, even if they are chopped over.

If the brothers are destroyed, ,such as burned to a crisp, they can be reanimate.

The Zombie Brothers only weakness is that they are dumb as a door-nail, but this is not really a problem when you are unkillarble.

The brothers are also cannibals, and would happily eat anyone if allowed by their boss, Liz Blood.

Defeating them is impossible for anyone but a elite demon.
name: Zombie Brothers

deck: Kith (vampire) who hunts his own kind.
description:
Origin

Brandom Alexander was once a normal man in love with Elizabeth. His life was destroyed when he fell prey to a band of rogue kith (vampires).In his struggle against the kith, he bit into one of their arms and drank his blood. They were too strong however, and left him for dead, taking Elizabeth with them. Waking up, he felt drained and crashed at his sister Tracy's place. She took care of him, but in his grief, he killed her by biting her neck and draining her blood. Desperate, he wanted to kill himself, but nothing worked. Instead of dying, he ultimately accepted his fate and vowed to take vengeance by destroying every kith which inhabited the Earth.

Another kith named Dougan found Brandon on the streets and decided to show Brandon how to live like a kith.

Created in a secret covert project for which only high ranking members of S.H.I.E.L.D. were privy to, including Director Maria Hill and Nick Fury.

deck: A Battleship-class Ubermensch aligned with the USSR.
description:
Current Events

Maria has currently been convinced by the USSR to rejoin the war effort and will likely be engaging in combat soon.

Origin

Many details of Maria's origin are currently unknown. She served in the Soviet Army as a Sniper and was nick named "The Manic Sniper" by her fellow troops.

Character Evolution

Maria was present at the Battle of Berlin when the Battleships and Panzermensch were first deployed. She even had the opportunity to snipe a Panzermensch Mark2 but failed due to its invulnerability. She managed to survive the battle and was taken as a POW.

She later, again managed to survive the mass execution of the near 1,000,000 prisoners, and eventually make her way back to the USSR. It is here she is eventually foreshadowed as a Battleship class Ubermensch.

Later when she and the other some 420,000 soldiers are back in Soviet lines, they are subjected to Wden's Blood in effort to create Tank-Men to counter Siegmund's task-force. Although initially appeared to be a failure, Maria is nevertheless revealed as a tank-men.

She fails her initial tests and displays no power unlike the others, this was due to the fact that she was in fact a Battleship and takes longer to mature. Maria later escapes the camp the Soviets are conducting experiments on and leaves out into the wilderness.

Making her way through Siberia, Maria eventually finds herself at the residence of an Elder couple who take her in and treat her as their own.

Before long the USSR Government finds her and although she initially resists - killing many soviets in the process she is eventually persuaded to go with them.

Personality

Maria appears to have some sort of psychological disorder and many of her fellow soldiers consider her crazy. She speaks with an childish demeanor. She often has nonsensical rumblings.

Powers and Abilities

Although the process is still being understood, the creation of Ubermensch begins with giving them treatments of an alien material known as Wden's Blood. Approximately one in five thousand humans can undertake treatments - those who cannot immediately die when touching the material.

Most humans can take three treatments, resulting it a common Panzermensch with enhanced speed, strength, invulnerability and an energy projection/manipulation ability referred to as distortion Halos. Later, different types of Ubermensch are created, some sacrificing their halo ability for greater physical prowess or vice versa.

Even rarer are humans who can handle more treatments of Wden's blood. The strongest being referred to as Battleships, which can handle a total of 24 treatments. Maria is one of these such Battleships.

Strength

Maria, as a battle-class ship Ubermensch is granted an enormous amount of strength. Although her own appearances are minor, her strength level should be around the 30+ ton range, fully capable of toss tanks around the battlefield.

Speed

She likewise is granted increased speed and should be capable of dodging gun and tankfire of the time.

Durability

Battleship class Ubermensch are completely invulnerable to all types of modern weaponry including small arms fire, tank fire, anti-tank fire and even recently Siegelinde has taken ship fired ordinance with no damage - although Maria has no unique showings of this.

Distortion Halos

Like all Ubermensch, Maria posses Distortion Halos, an energy projection and manipulation type ability. Other battleships are capable of wiping out bombers and tanks in mass with casual ease and can wipe other V2s just as easily.Battleship Class Distoration Halos are also the only known effective weapon against other Battleships.

They also demonstrate matter manipulation with their Halos. Maria herself has been able to transmute the earth into food to sustain herself.

Fatigue

All Ubermensch suffer a weakness of fatigue. In this state they are incredible vulnerable and can be killed much more easily. Although the Battleships themselves display a very high tolerance against this weakness, they still suffer from it. Klaudia was incapacitated for days by being over deployed for a period of 6 hours.

Although the exact time limit for the Battleships deployment is not yet known, it seems a period of about 12 hours of continual combat before stopping for rest is ideal. Still, each Battleship is fully capable of supporting an entire German front.
name: Katyusha
